            <title>[JCR-1818] Too many open files when merging large index segments</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/JCR-1818</link>
                <project id="10591" key="JCR">Jackrabbit Content Repository</project>
                        <description>When large index segments are merged it may happen that lots of smaller index segments are created but have to wait until the large&lt;br/&gt;
index merge has completed. This may lead to a &amp;#39;too many open files&amp;#39; exception on some system.&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
We should find a solution where large index merges are better decoupled from regular index operations.</description>
